Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar yawan 'yan kasar da ke dauke da cutar HIV da Aids da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne cutar ta shafa a ƙasar.
Kimanin sabbin mutane 40,000 aka bayar da rahoton a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka an kai su ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wajen ƙarin jini da ke ɗauke da cutar.
Amma yawan mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da Aids a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT ta kasar Sin.
An dakatar da nuna luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana cewa nuna wariya ga mutanen LGBT ya zama ruwan dare.
Domin al'adar ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin cututtukan cututtuka suna zuwa ne daga rashin isasshen kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin cewa kowa zai iya samun maganin cutar HIV a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
